\begin_layout Subsubsection
Ultrafast operation with Adabatic Rapid Passage pulse
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are two kinds of entanglement gates proposed in the trapped ion system
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "PhysRevA.71.062309"
literal "false"

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "roos_ion_2008"
literal "false"

\end_inset

: the 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{\sigma_{z}}}$
\end_inset

 gate and the 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{\phi}$
\end_inset

 gate.
 They both create spin-depentent force to accumulate desired phase in the
 phae space.
 To realize entangment between ions' internal state, first step will be
 entangment between motional states and internal states which uses motional
 state as the quantum bus.
 At the end of the gate, the motional state and internal state will decouple
 which become another limitaion factor.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{z}$
\end_inset

 gate will create driven spin-dependent stack shift between the qubit energy
 levels and not create qubit flipping.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{\phi}$
\end_inset

 will create qubit flipping accompanying with the spin-dependent momentum
 kicks.
 These kind of gate provides ultrafast speed even higher than the speed
 of the gate, which accesss Lamb-Dicke limit.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi/2$
\end_inset

pulse creates spin-denpendent kick force and one need to optimize the number
 and distribution of the kicks sequence.
 Recent research shows progresses in this area: 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "mizrahi_quantum_2014"
literal "false"

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "wong-campos_demonstration_2017"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 with mode-locked laser and create the two qubits entanglement gate.
 DISANDVANTAGE
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here we propose to use strong foucs Adiabatic Rapid Pulse to realize the
 spin-dependent kick sequence, which also used in atom interferometry which
 seperate paths of differnt energy level and accumlate the phase between
 differnt paths.
 There have been large areas and momentum transfers proposed recently 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "kotru_large-area_2015"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 The Adiabatic Rapid Passage is also used in the ion trap on states shutling
 and motional states cooling.
 We find that with increase the power of pulses which is the requirement
 of addressing single ion and optimize the parameters, we can achieve the
 high speed and fidelity single qubit flipping and two qubit entanglement
 gate.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We make a model of eight energy level 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{171Yb^{+}}}$
\end_inset

 ions which shows in Fig.
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:EightEnergyLevel"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 The qubits are encoded in the ground hyperfine states of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{171Yb^{+}}}$
\end_inset

 ions: 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2S_{1/2}|F=0,m_{F}=0>}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\textrm{\textrm{\mathbf{\textrm{\textrm{2S_{1/2}|F=1,m_{F}=0>}}}}}$
\end_inset

 with an energy spliting 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{HF}=2\pi\times12.6428$
\end_inset

 GHz.
 The raman beams are detuning by hundreds of GHz to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

and they are far less than the 100 THz spiltting between 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{3/2}}}$
\end_inset

.
 So we do not need to consider the coupling to the 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{3/2}}}$
\end_inset

and only see 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

as the virtual energy level.
 The hyperfine splitting between 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

is 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{1}=2\pi\times2105$
\end_inset

 MHz.
 We consider the zeeman effect (
\begin_inset Formula $2\pi\times1.4$
\end_inset

 MHz/G for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2S_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $2\pi\times0.47$
\end_inset

 MHz/G for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

) and quadratic effect (
\begin_inset Formula $2\pi\times310.8$
\end_inset

Hz/
\begin_inset Formula $G^{2}$
\end_inset

) for 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{171Yb^{+}}}$
\end_inset

 zeeman splitting.
 Then we can define:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
2S_{1/2}|F=0,m_{F}=0>\equiv|0>
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
2S_{1/2}|F=1,m_{F}=0>\equiv|1>
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
2P_{1/2}|F=1,m_{F}=-1>\equiv|2>
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
2P_{1/2}|F=1,m_{F}=1>\equiv|3>
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "fig:EightEnergyLevel"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Graphics
	filename C:/Users/scientist/Desktop/haoqing/Fastgate/kick/fig/eight_level.svg
	lyxscale 80

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

-polarized light cannot drive dipole transition between qubit states and
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{\textrm{2P_{1/2}}}$
\end_inset

 energy level for corresponding dipole matrixs equal to zero.
 Because:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sigma_{x}=1/2(\sigma^{+}+\sigma^{-})
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sigma_{y}=1/2(\sigma^{+}-\sigma^{-}),
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
with 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{+}$
\end_inset

can couple between 
\begin_inset Formula $|0>,|1>$
\end_inset

to 
\begin_inset Formula $|2>$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma^{+}$
\end_inset

can couple between 
\begin_inset Formula $|0>,|1>$
\end_inset

to 
\begin_inset Formula $|3>$
\end_inset

, we apply 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{x}$
\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{y}$
\end_inset

 polarization light to drive the raman process.
 The intensity of the bichromatic lights are set to satisfy the condition:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{I_{x}}{I_{y}}=\frac{\Delta-\delta_{0}}{\Delta+\delta_{0}}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
for AC-stark shifts are proportional to 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{I}{\Delta}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{I_{x}}{\Delta}+\frac{I_{y}}{\Delta+12.6}=\frac{I_{y}}{\Delta}+\frac{I_{x}}{\Delta-12.6}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
to cancel the AC-stark shift on the qubit level caused by two lights and
 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta$
\end_inset

is the single-phonon detuning.
 Adabatic Rapid Passage we used here is similer to methods derived from
 nucler resonmance.
 For the Raman ARP, the whole system can be viewed as an effective two-level
 system: the rabi frequency is the two-phonon 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega_{eff}$
\end_inset

 here; the detuning across the resonance is the two-phonon detuning sweeping
 during the invertion of population, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta(t)=\delta_{HF}-(w_{y}-w_{x})$
\end_inset

.
 The Bloch vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\text{\ensuremath{\vec{s}}}$
\end_inset

 will precesses around the effective routation axis 
\begin_inset Formula $|\Omega(t)|=\sqrt{\Omega_{eff}^{2}(t)+\delta^{2}(t)}$
\end_inset

, and satisfy:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\frac{d\vec{s}}{dt}=\vec{\Omega}\times\vec{s}
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
if the Bloch vector can adabaticly follow the 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{\Omega}$
\end_inset

.
 We generate the fast ARP pulse with the Intensity envelope 
\begin_inset Formula $I(t)$
\end_inset

 and two-phonon detuning with the form following:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
I_{x,y}(t)=I_{x,y}\\sin(\pi t/\tau)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\delta(t)=\delta_{0}\cos^{2}(\pi t/\tau)
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

